## 1. Purpose

This policy establishes {{ business_name }}'s rules for retaining, archiving, and destroying data that is processed by, generated by, or stored within AI systems. It ensures compliance with **APP 11** (security and destruction of personal information) of the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and supports the organisation's obligations under the **AI6 Guidance for AI Adoption** (Practice 3: Measure and Manage Risks).

---

## 2. Scope

This policy applies to all data that interacts with AI systems, including:

- **AI inputs** — prompts, queries, uploaded documents, and data submitted to AI tools
- **AI outputs** — generated text, code, images, recommendations, and decisions
- **AI interaction logs** — records of prompts, responses, timestamps, and user identifiers
- **AI training data** — any organisational data used to fine-tune or train AI models
- **AI-inferred data** — profiles, predictions, scores, and classifications generated by AI

