## 4. Destruction Methods

When data reaches the end of its retention period, it must be destroyed using methods appropriate to its classification:

| Classification | Destruction Method | Verification |
|---------------|-------------------|-------------|
| Public / Internal | Permanent deletion from AI tool accounts and local storage | Deletion confirmation |
| Confidential | Secure deletion with overwrite; request vendor deletion confirmation | Written vendor confirmation |
| Restricted | Cryptographic erasure or certified destruction; vendor deletion certificate | Destruction certificate retained for 12 months |

### 4.1 AI-Specific Destruction Requirements

- **AI tool accounts:** Review and purge conversation histories, saved prompts, and uploaded files at retention expiry
- **Vendor-hosted AI:** Submit data deletion requests to AI vendors; obtain written confirmation
- **AI model training:** If organisational data was used to fine-tune a model, request the vendor confirm the model has been retrained without your data, or that training data has been purged
- **Cached/derived data:** Ensure AI-inferred data (predictions, profiles, embeddings) is also destroyed — not just source data

{% if ai_tools_overseas and ai_tools_overseas | length > 0 %}
### 4.2 Cross-Border Destruction

For AI tools that process data overseas, {{ business_name }} must:
- Verify destruction has occurred in all data centre locations (APP 8 obligations persist until destruction)
- Obtain written destruction confirmation from overseas vendors
- Retain destruction certificates for 12 months
{% endif %}

