## 5. De-Identification as an Alternative

Where full destruction is not practicable (e.g., data embedded in aggregate models), {{ business_name }} may de-identify data as permitted under APP 11.2. De-identification must ensure the information is no longer "about an identifiable individual" per the Privacy Act definition.

De-identification methods:
- Remove direct identifiers (names, email, ABN, account numbers)
- Generalise quasi-identifiers (age ranges instead of dates of birth, state instead of suburb)
- Apply k-anonymity or differential privacy where technically feasible

